  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of WASH &amp; FSL support to vulnerable IDPs and host communities in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project targets vulnerable beneficiaries who include IDPs,Returnees and Host Communities regardless of age and gender of affected communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of the following to 33,000 people - IDPs and host affected by conflicts and drought
-	Cash grant (conditional for livelihoods)
-	Crop/veg seeds &amp; farming tools distribution
-	Cash for work
-	Training on livelihoods &amp; agriculture skills
-	Drilling shallow borehole (by manual drill) in Upper Nile and /or installation of SWAT (one spare set now in Upper Nile)
-	Drilling deep borehole (by mechanic drill) in Unity
-	Construction of emergency latrines in IDP settlements
-	Hygiene promotion</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide life saving intervention to IDP and Host communities and reduce hygiene and sanitation disease</narrative>
  </description>
